Procedure
Step 1: Install Hyperledger Fabric
Download Fabric samples:
curl -sSL https://bit.ly/2ysbOFE | bash -s

Move to test network:
cd fabric-samples/test-network

Step 2: Start Blockchain Network:
./network.sh up createChannel -ca
Output:
Creating channel 'mychannel'
Network started successfully

Step 3: Deploy Chaincode:
./network.sh deployCC -ccn rewards -ccp ../asset-transfer-basic/chaincode-javascript -ccl javascript
Output:
Chaincode committed successfully

Step 4: Install Node.js Packages:
npm init -y

Install required packages:
npm install express fabric-network fabric-ca-client body-parser

Step 5: Create Web Server
app.js:
const express = require('express');
const app = express();
app.use(express.json());
app.post('/member', async (req, res) => {
const member = {
id: req.body.id,
name: req.body.name,
points: req.body.points
};
res.send("Member Added Successfully");
});
app.get('/member/:id', async (req, res) => {
res.send("Display Member Reward Points");
});
app.listen(3000, () => {
console.log("Server running on port 3000");
});

Step 6: Run Application
Start server:
node app.js
Output
Server running on port 3000

Step 7: Test Using Browser or Postman
Create Member
URL:
POST http://localhost:3000/member
JSON Input:
{
"id":"M101",
"name":"Rahul",
"points":"100"
}
Output
Member Added Successfully

Read Member Reward Points
URL:
GET http://localhost:3000/member/M101
Output:
{
"id":"M101",
"name":"Rahul",
"points":"100"
}

Chaincode Interaction Commands
Invoke Transaction:
peer chaincode invoke -C mychannel -n rewards \
-c '{"Args":["createMember","M101","Rahul","100"]}'

Query Transaction:
peer chaincode query -C mychannel -n rewards \
-c '{"Args":["readMember","M101"]}'
